   Kothic  Map Renderer

   The maintained project overview, Python 3 test command, and fork
   compatibility notes live in README.md. This legacy README is kept so old
   links to the original renderer instructions do not break.
   
   Depends:
   1. tWMS http://twms.googlecode.com/
     symlink twms directory into src/
   2. python-lxml
   3. python-psyco, if available.
   4. pygtk for GUI
   5. pycairo
   6. python-psycopg2
   7. python-shapely
   8. python-pyproj

   To run the legacy tile import example:
   1. Install all dependencies.
   2. Download a small OSM XML extract, for example from Geofabrik,
      BBBike, Overpass, or another public OSM extract provider.
   3. Save it as small_test_osm_dump.osm, or replace the filename below
      with the path to your own extract.
   4. cd src/
   5. cat ../small_test_osm_dump.osm | python osm2tiles.py
   6. wait a bit and check if tiles got generated
   7. python kothic.py to run GUI

   The filename small_test_osm_dump.osm was only an example input dump name;
   this repository does not ship a canonical sample dump.

   To run the maintained Python 3 test suite, follow README.md from the
   repository root.

   NOT READY FOR DAILY USAGE!
